Re: Retainer Agreement for Consulting Services on behalf of Catelli Brothers, Inc.
This Letter of Understanding will confirm to you our commitment in providing you and the
management team of Catelli Brothers, Inc. with consulting services during the attempt by the a
union to organize your workforce, and to set forth the Terms and Conditions for said consulting
services on behalf of Catelli Brothers, Inc. in said campaign. Further, this Letter of Understanding
shall be valid and in force for the duration of our representation of Catelli Brothers, Inc..
As you may be aware, organizations facing labor campaigns today are confronted with ever
greater obstacles from the unions, as well as the federal government (i.e., the National Labor
Relations Board). It should be recognized that, given the aggressiveness of the union leaders on
a national and local level, Unfair Labor Practices (ULPs) and election objections are becoming
ever more routine in labor campaigns:
As part of Kulture Consulting's Client Commitment, efforts will continually be
made, in concert with labor counsel, to avert sustained ULP charges and/or
election objections. However, given the increased pro-union case rulings, it
should be expected that ULPs and/or election objections, though uncommon
and infrequent, may be filed and potentially sustained even on the basis of well-
established and/or legally sanctioned written material and/or verbal
presentations by persons internal (e.g., supervision/management) or external
Although efforts will continually be made and precautions taken to avert the
filing of ULP charges and/or objections, itshould be understood that individuais
within and/or external to Catelli Brothers, Inc. cannot and shall not be held liable,
nor accountable, for that which occurs with regard to potential union-filed ULPs
As per prior discussion, the cost of Kulture Consulting's services is at a consulting rate
of $275 per hour, per consultant, and $200 per hour for all other consultants, including
travel plus actual and reasonable expenses.
Invoices will be provided to Catelli Brothers, Inc. on an orgoing basis. All invoices
shall be paid by Catelli Brothers, Inc. upon receipt.
This contract may be terminated, at any time, by either party involved, with payment for
work hours expended since the last billing through dates/times of termination, plus
actual and reasonable expenses incurred, to be paid in full.
Upon engagement of our services, please acknowledge receipt and approval of the above
stipulations regarding representation/consulting services, invoicing, and payment.
As appropriate, we would appreciate the opportunity to assist you in this important challenge.
